        </div>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         And those numbers are
         <em>
          pre
         </em>
         -COVID. According to a
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVUctu2zAQ_BrxFoOiLIk68OCkTRogTnvrkeBjJbPhQ-Cjhv--lBygLUCQy1nMDLmjRIYlxBtbQ8qoJIjcaNYOhHb9cUKaHXVLe4pM4nMEcMJYlmMBtBZpjRLZBL8zMCY9ujCg89wLMkI_q5l2I9ZKTqOQo9TDSAeMNh8uijbgFTD4DfEWPCDLLjmvqelODXmu65dwwkO-hvhxUMFtSCjRC5v-b4YVfEXmYq2I2SgL9UbGEbfHoemeS3Y8VaKCpvvyYoMUtiGP30DYfKnF-_efdT8LUzUe30zKDRk2ihJuFWbxlTTLiY5UaCIfvp5Pr2_86XT-cXp9eecEE8zxxHHHMeG4_-Q60Ka4ytyH9QlmiBuEOdVY44FoqR_-USZ0whS3yLBNtG3x1HY97cihPfQ-LtcoWqmhOWK3kEMqMmWh9rmgyHzIMkTjl9r-uAgHdm_UfHg9XfEm3zh4IS3oe3T5HvaeRL6twDxck4VcH3kHtzwpnkidI6puOtSf-L9GfwAGH7wR" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          JAMA Network Survey
         </a>
         , depressive symptoms have tripled during the pandemic.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The total direct and indirect costs of the mental health epidemic are expected to reach
         <em>
          <strong>
           $6 trillion
          </strong>
         </em>
         by 2030, up from $2.5 trillion in 2010, according to the World Economic Forum. The Lancet Commission estimates that number to be as high as $16 trillion when you include the loss of productivity, and spending on social welfare, education, and law and order. Despite the huge need, the last real innovation in the fight against mental illness was the release of Prozac in 1988.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         After fifty years in the dark, though, psychedelics are once again getting the chance to shine. Led by public figures like Michael Pollan, Tim Ferriss, and even Joe Rogan, and leading institutions like Johns Hopkins, NYU, Berkeley, and Imperial College London, therapeutic psychedelics are going mainstream again:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           On election night, Oregon voted to
           <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEmOhDAMRU9T2QVlgCpYZNGbvgbKYCCqDChDI_r0HYpFS5Gt5Nv-ztOywBrTKfaYC6oZ0myNoE828qGfkBG9oeMwIpvnJQF4aZ0oqQLaq3JWy2Jj-HQQwga0iReXPX0tymjF9cCfGqYJ-LNfOCPQt5LLZ5bVWAgaBPxAOmMA5MRWyp4f_OvBvts5jqPTQelOR9-ujDDSEqUtkL6FmNraAStoOmS82JQLzqX9BpeIHazS2V_AXq5WY1_zlmL0GcuMfWu9KzMGmQGbVFfs5JG7rXiHrLjMKCUT5cPIWUe7IaT1SJIqA4-e-JV1uao2Qr-v9VASIRYVkw1rk9-b9OA-QmM0t-xrsOWcIUjlwNz4yg38Q6OcO4gAR3ZQCqT78WI6komx1ws1NxMb-vBv9AcRqpdr" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
            legalize psilocybin
           </a>
           for mental health treatment in supervised settings. Washington, DC voted to decriminalize it.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           The FDA granted Breakthrough Therapy Designation, which they grant to therapies that have shown great promise and clinically significant improvement over available therapies, to three trials using psychedelics to treat mental health indications, one with MDMA and two with psilocybin, the active ingredient in magic mushrooms.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Last week, Johns Hopkins released a
           <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkUGOpDAMRU9T2YFCKLpgkUVv-hooJL8hUyRBsRnE7SdUlTSSJVv-sr79bA1jTvnUWyIWOyGP3unmS_Vtdx-E03fX9F0vPI2_GQjGr5rzDrHt0-qtYZ_ia0JK1YlFA5N0bWecedgJrVPK3RvIXyuHL2ftIC6f0ezOI1po_EU-U4RY9cK80a39vqmfEsdx1Evanj5SgPPWR9Qpz0WJOOiTckrhU1YZKwzhkjY67QKHsl_FGYYDIleH56XayK_JnpOP14Av9lQF8yflymHLICrnVMS7Oyta0kHCayWVbBo5NG3Xt6pu6i7m-cimmRxudxlmVdM-ERv7rG0KIuuYeErZx7nIz8UErC-hEBtLDnv0fI6IZlrh3jD5jf_Fhs8N-jppBTPyu3kR7uWg1OMhiptL5RHxv9E_Z3Gh2A" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
            new study
           </a>
           that showed that treatment with psilocybin and supportive psychotherapy produced rapid and large reductions in depressive symptoms in adults with major depression, with a magnitude of effect
           <strong>
            four times larger
           </strong>
           than antidepressants\xe2\x80\x99.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         At this point, you might be thinking: dope. This sounds amazing. Give people shrooms! But this isn\xe2\x80\x99t a healthcare newsletter. Not Boring isn\xe2\x80\x99t
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMuKxCAQ_JrxGNS8zMHDXuY3go9OIjEatN0hf79OclhoaKiiqIdRCGtMlzxjRlIypNlZyQYu2r6biJWdZaIXxOV5SQCHcl5iKkDOor0zCl0Mt4JS3pOtKmEYKXBjBzrBQheqR2XbSbTULBo0-frMqlgHwYCEX0hXDEC83BDP_Gp_XvxdLxaMyxnNDthsoDxuFSROcsopY3RibS9a3rCmD2n9JMW0hVdHj5U3ueiMyuyNiQdJMkTUMbmwVnrf1AH-Jmr-uf6jBIfXDEFpD_aphs8Yd1K8TpABPtkDIqQH_PYVdOJ8HEl1s7HOEv6N_gAamnU5" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Out of Pocket
         </a>
         . Why are you telling me this?
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In September,
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMGOhSAQ-xo5GkBROXDYy_6GQZlV8hAIDGv8-0U9bDLJZNo0nXbVCFtIl4ohIykZ0myNYgOfOtFLYlRv2CQmYvP8kwAObZ3CVIDEsji7arTBPwpKuSC7YqMQ_SA5G9eBg2Sy52KZhgGMqMA4kNtn1sVY8Cso-IV0BQ_EqR0x5qb7avh3nTUcUeccNe6nvnJb74oSqzjllDEqWSemjresFT5tZ9JsMdD09Nh4m8uSUa-fW0SS8gGXkKzfKv3Z9QHuIWqAue6jeIvXDF4vDsybDd82nlfxiqA8nNkBIqQXvANPVHI-jqS6mVB78f9GfyYOdCE" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          COMPASS Pathways
         </a>
         (
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMtqxDAM_Jr4GGzn5Rx8KAu9FQr9gOCHNjHr2MFWuuTv6ySHgkCPQTMaGYUwx3TILWYke4Y0OStZz0XTtSOxsrVMdIK4PD0TwKqcl5h2INuuvTMKXQzXBqW8I4tsG9ZqxgfDoe9bxQWwngmh7fBkHaMjOXUmtVsHwYCEX0hHDEC8XBC3XDUfFf8scdPXJq6lyRjNK5fi8fX9Q5zklFNWyFjTiYbXrO5Cmt9JMW2hauk68zrvOqMyr5OBJBki6phcmAv8WtQK_gKKylTyugeHxwRBaQ_29of3R65z8dhABnhnD4iQ7uFpWtCR82EgRc3G8pvwL_QHmmV05A" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          NASDAQ: CMPS
         </a>
         ) IPO\xe2\x80\x99d and became the first public company with a psilocybin-based product.
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUEuOhSAQPM1jSQBxxAWL2cw1DJ9WyUMw0I7x9sPTxSSddLoqnfo4g7Dkcuk9VyRHhTIFr_mXUF0vR-K19Fz1ioQ6zQVgMyFqLAeQ_bAxOIMhp_uDMdGTVUvpBsFnKZlRHrzlTHEJHVPSCDn3lnx0JnP4AMmBhl8oV05Aol4R9_rqvl_ip815ntSgCTSGGdpNghZMMM7ZyLtedYJy2qeynMVw6-El2bYIWg9b0bg3dXkjRaeMNpeQlka_V7NBvIlmfWp7O1LAa4JkbAT_pMKnh9skXjvoBGeNgAjlAT9RFRuFGAbS1HxujaR_oT-y2HIV" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          ATAI Life Sciences
         </a>
         , a \xe2\x80\x9cbiotech platform to heal mental health disorders\xe2\x80\x9d with a wide range of psychedelic-based therapies, recently raised a round from investors like Peter Thiel and Michael Novogratz and is expected to go public soon.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         It\xe2\x80\x99s tempting to group psychedelics companies like COMPASS in with the \xe2\x80\x9cgreen wave\xe2\x80\x9d of cannabis companies that have taken the market by storm starting with Tilray\xe2\x80\x99s IPO in July 2018. But psychedelics companies like COMPASS are less like cannabis companies, which have mainly focused on recreational use, and more like biotech stocks focused on the hardest-to-tackle mental health indications. ATAI\xe2\x80\x99s
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMuKwzAM_Jr6GGw5aZODD0thL_sRwY7U1NSxg61syN-v0x4WBEIahnlMlmlO-TBrKiy2Qnn0aNQVet21g0DTouq7XvgyPjLRYn0wnDcS6-aCnyz7FN8MKaETTwNa227SiPbR4lWhQ3S2BQUA_fU2gDh1RruhpziRoV_KR4okgnkyr-Wivy7wXYd3z0y5mdJSrx-iQPmego_CG5AglZKD0l2voVFNF_O8Z6sc0qWVywxN2VxhO71OvsgmJnYp-zhX-PW0C4U3UDOMdS9b9HyMFK0LhJ94_Cnk7ZaPlUykvQQ6PX2eZ-ZeDgC3m6hqmGo18V_oD5nCdkE" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Colin Keeler
         </a>
         told me:
        </p>
        <blockquote style="border-left: 4px solid #67bdfc; margin: 1em 0;">
         <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1em;">
          <em>
           We\xe2\x80\x99re seeing increasing acceptance across investor classes - traditional biotech investors, Silicon Valley, family offices. The biggest names and the best analysts in the space are approaching psychedelics with real sincerity, and the government to a large extent is approaching them the same way, because mental health disorders have such a large unmet need.
          </em>
         </p>
        </blockquote>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The research reports back him up.
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkT1vwyAQhn9N2LAAm8YZGKpKVZdIGbp0ss7mHKNgsOBcy_--OBkqoTu4r_f0MADhPabdLDETWzOmzlkj31Rb6-bCrGmsbHXLXO7GhDiD84bSimxZe-8GIBfDs0MIpdlkWmVhFK04C6mlFnBuetHA2OrG9mh7yw6dDlbrMAxo8BfTHgMybyaiJZ_q95P6LGdwlGJImBHSMFVDnEtwW_gQA2Gg8lgXH8HmclNCieLkYT7ivEDO_AY0bbBn_j0hv3mgMaaZX0sreP6F4Gniz9qwcy34T5HJ3AVOpfwKDxfu1WJH5swxXEpxkbVua1XJSod03xLI3uKpEfNdVXntM8HwOLZkyYRIfUxlQkk_JpjRPxMFWFf8vAZHe4cBeo_2xZJe9J9oaF_QBNyyRyJMr-ABuBUXpc5nVtRsLP8Q_oX-AB3jm6Y" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Citron Research
         </a>
         , best known as an activist short fund, gushed uncharacteristically when it called COMPASS, \xe2\x80\x9cthe most compelling IPO of the year whose
         <strong>
          significance to humanity has the potential to be a generational stock
         </strong>
         .\xe2\x80\x9d
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Here\xe2\x80\x99s the crazy thing. Most hot IPOs feature companies whose products weren\xe2\x80\x99t even imaginable a decade or two ago. We\xe2\x80\x99ve been studying psilocybin\xe2\x80\x99s benefits for
         <em>
          62 years
         </em>
         . What the hell took us so long?
        </p>
        <h3 style="color: #1a1a1a; font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;">
         <strong>
          The War On Drugs
         </strong>
        </h3>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In this time of vicious political division in the United States, I think there\xe2\x80\x99s one thing that all Americans can agree on: Richard Nixon was a real dick.
        </p>
        <a class="youtube-wrap" href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMtugzAQ_Bp8RLYxxBx8qBSl-YGekR8bsAI2steh_H0hOVRaaaUZ7c7DaoQxpl2tMSMpGdLgnWIdl00reuKUcEy2kvg8PBLAov2sMBUgazGztxp9DO8LSnlLJiW1E6zrjOglbWxvwOiLcdKBcFR0D0lOnUEX5yFYUPCCtMcAZFYT4pqr5qvit2O2bav3WLAYqG1cTkSjnarm9qqaa3f_-b3bbzs8I_GKU04Zoz1rWtnwmtVtSOOWNDMOKkGXkde5mIzaPs9fJKkQ0cTkw3jQz0kvML-JI9Nw7KUEj_sAQZsZ3Ccufgp6u8d9BRVgyzMgQvqAZweS9pxfLuRQc_GoKvwL_QHpNXtt" style="display: block; margin: 1.6em 0;" target="_blank">
         <img src="https://cdn.substack.com/image/youtube/w_550,c_limit/l_youtube_play_qyqt8q,w_120/6HUxHcGc_ko" style="-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none !important; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0 auto; max-width: 550px; vertical-align: middle; width: 100%;"/>
        </a>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In addition to being the Watergate guy, in 1971, Nixon declared a
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMGOhCAQRL9muI0BFMUDh73sbxiQHocdBdPAGv9-25nDJoSudKUo8mZbYEl4mj3lwmoGnII3ope6Vd3IvOm80EqzkKcHAmw2rKZgBbZXt4bZlpDiO8G5VOxp3Oh66AfbidbPXav7h1R29NKO2vdSeXb1TLb6AHEGA7-AZ4rAVvMsZc-39usmv-kcx9HYDZAq4o5pQci5SbiQFXKukEnMGLYQ7Xr_qbmEGWiFsCcslym50DR4f-mBrk5JLUYSEH2Iy_2wePdYl3yPdXOAV4gFIzklBR9Fq3QrG9GoiMuBVjgPt45vi2xydbnY-dXMaWNoYiouIT1J9utJn17fBgGaaG41hnJOEK1bwX_YlQ_tN4py7mAiHHmFUgA_ywuo5qOUw8CozSfiHv-L_gCLF5Rk" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          War on Drugs
         </a>
         that has, among other evils, cost the United States over $1 trillion, disproportionately targeted Black people, and led to an arrest for drug possession
         <em>
          every 25 seconds
         </em>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The War on Drugs cost millions of American lives and prevented tens of millions more from their Constitutional right to the pursuit of happiness. It\xe2\x80\x99s the reason that we lump all Schedule One drugs together as \xe2\x80\x9cbad and dangerous\xe2\x80\x9d despite their vastly different profiles, while doctors happily write prescriptions for the opioids that
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMuOwyAM_JpyjIA0LTlw2Mv-RgTYTdDyiMA0m79f2h5WsmSPR_ZoxhnCNZdT77kSaxXL4kGLm1TjdJ0Z6CsINSnm6_IoiNH4oKk0ZHuzwTtDPqf3BedyYps2kxjVLFBZK0H2PxLR2Rs4UGjG24O9dBbTwGNyqPGJ5cwJWdAb0V4v49dFfvc6jmNw4IY1PzuC0vqABXLFDnH3gNG7PvoE-DtsFAPzWnLJheCzGCc1ykEMUyrrUYywgJcrj6scarOVjPsZXI6s6JTJ5uLT2umfzUQMb6KbW3qPLXk6F0zGBoSPb_ok9bZB54464VEDEmH5LF9hKD5Leb-zrga5Z5b-hf4AFGp_pg" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          kill 128 Americans every day
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         So why\xe2\x80\x99d he do it?
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In 1955, a New York banker named R. Gordon Wasson went to Mexico in search of a god-like mushroom, and detailed his experiences in a 1957 Life Magazine article called \xe2\x80\x9c
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMuOwyAM_JpyRGCSlhw47GV_I4LgJmh5ROBslL9f2h5WsmRrRtY8Fku4lnqZvTRiR8M6B2_kHbQah4l5M3ipR81Cm58VMdkQDdUD2X64GBZLoeT3hxAwss0AqIfDJyzOD1ppYaWGQXkB8u7V5Dx76cz28AHzggZ_sV4lI4tmI9pv6usG333O8-Qh2TVkW4Plpa4v0LZWcj9ieCLfKLFgQICQUkxSjVoBl3zMdT2rlc7jbRBpBd4O18guP3wpiVWTC7lSQ147_bPZhPFN9Dxz3-nIga4Zs3UR_Scqfcp5O6drR5PxbBGJsH7AV34tJoDHg3U1X3pN-V_oD8yUeg4" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Seeking the Magic Mushroom
         </a>
         ,\xe2\x80\x9d bringing the experience into the western consciousness. He also brought psilocybin into the lab. He sent mushroom samples to Albert Hofmann, a Sandoz scientist who had previously discovered LSD, and in 1958, Hofmann isolated the chemical structure of the active compound. By 1960, Sandoz released Psilocybin pills under the name Indocybin.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; text-align: center;">
         <figure style="display: inline-block; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" style="margin: 1.6em auto; mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
