        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The War on Drugs was like the Food Pyramid on crack, tricking generations of Americans into making unhealthy decisions despite the best intentions. Nixon started it, and Raegan picked up where he left off, waging an all-out media offensive. In 1987, the Partnership for a Drug-Free America dropped the classic \xe2\x80\x9cThis is Your Brain on Drugs\xe2\x80\x9d commercial.
        </p>
