        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Far from killing brain cells, psilocybin rewires the brain and forms rich new connections, at least temporarily, between parts of the brains that don\xe2\x80\x99t normally speak to each other. That\xe2\x80\x99s why people report seeing music or tasting colors when they\xe2\x80\x99re tripping.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The bad press and propaganda surrounding mushrooms, largely a remnant of the culture wars of the early 1970s and late 1980s, obfuscates their incredible therapeutic promise.
        </p>
